asks)\n    SendComplete { send_id: u64, result: SendResult },\n\n    // Incoming messages (from coordinator/node background pollers)\n    IncomingMessage { envelope: Box<OuterEnvelope>, source: MessageSource },\n\n    // Outbox tick results (from spawned outbox task)\n    OutboxTickResult(Result<(usize, usize, u64), String>),\n\n    // Node events\n    NodeError(String),\n}\n```\n\n### Key invariant\n\n**`update()` is synchronous** (or at most does trivial local DB reads). It never does network I/O. Any operation that touches the network goes through `tokio::spawn` → result back via `action_tx`. This is enforced structurally: `update()` takes `&mut self` (no `async`), so you literally cannot `.await` inside it.\n\n### Send flow (the actual fix for #99)\n\n1. User presses Enter → `Action::Key(Enter)` \n2. `update()` handles it:\n   - `prepare_message()` (sync: crypto + local DB write)\n   - Create `Message` with `DeliveryStatus::Sending` and a monotonic `send_id`\n   - Display optimistically\n   - Clone `client`, clone `action_tx`, spawn:\n     ```rust\n     tokio::spawn(async move {\n         let result = client.submit_and_record(...).await;\n         let _ = action_tx.send(Action::SendComplete { send_id, result });\n     });\n     ```\n   - Clear input\n3. When `Action::SendComplete` arrives → `update()` finds the message by `send_id`, updates `DeliveryStatus` to `Sent(phase)` or `Failed(error)`\n\n### Message struct change\n\n```rust\n#[derive(Debug, Clone)]\npub struct Message {\n    pub from_me: bool,\n    pub sender_name: String,\n    pub content: String,\n    pub timestamp: String,\n    pub status: DeliveryStatus,  // NEW\n}\n\n#[derive(Debug, Clone, Default)]\npub enum DeliveryStatus {\n    #[default]\n    None,           // received messages, no status needed\n    Sending,        // optimistic display, awaiting result\n    Sent(String),   // delivery phase description\n    Failed(String), // error description\n}\n```\n\n### Incoming message handling\n\nCurrently `coordinator_events.try_recv()` and `node_event_rx.try_recv()` are polled inline. Under the new architecture, these become background drainer tasks that forward into `action_tx`:\n\n```rust\n// Spawned once at startup\ntokio::spawn(async move {\n    while let Some(event) = coordinator_events.recv().await {\n        if let TransportEvent::Message(envelope) = event {\n            let _ = action_tx.send(Action::IncomingMessage {\n                envelope: Box::new(envelope),\n                source: MessageSource::Coordinator,\n            });\n        }\n    }\n});\n```\n\nSame pattern for `node_event_rx`. This eliminates all `try_recv` polling from the main loop.\n\n### Main loop\n\n```rust\npub async fn run(&mut self, terminal: &mut Terminal<impl Backend>) -> AppResult<()> {\n    let mut event_handler = EventHandler::new(100);\n\n    // spawn background drainers (coordinator, node, outbox tick)\n    self.spawn_background_tasks();\n\n    while self.running {\n        // Wait for next event OR action\n        tokio::select! {\n            event = event_handler.next() => {\n                let action = match event? {\n                    Event::Key(k) => Action::Key(k),\n                    Event::Tick => Action::Tick,\n                    Event::Resize(w, h) => Action::Resize(w, h),\n                };\n                self.update(action);\n            }\n            Some(action) = self.action_rx.recv() => {\n                self.update(action);\n            }\n        }\n\n        // Drain any additional queued actions\n        while let Ok(action) = self.action_rx.try_recv() {\n            self.update(action);\n        }\n\n        // Render after processing all pending actions\n        terminal.draw(|frame| ui::render(frame, self))?;\n    }\n\n    self.shutdown().await;\n    Ok(())\n}\n```\n\n### What changes, what doesn't\n\n| Component | Change |\n|-----------|--------|\n| `Message` struct | Add `status: DeliveryStatus` field |\n| `App` struct | Add `action_